						               													<description>MathMINDs Games are storybook board games that combine math, history and literacy in a highly connected experience. Through each story, you&amp;#202;&amp;#188;ll learn and play games as you explore real events from the game's country of origin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Achi is a historical game played in Ghana that is very similar to Tic-tac-toe. Add in a connection to the magic square from ancient China and you have the recipe for a storybook board game that shows how math connects different cultures around the world!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The four unique species of butterflies found on Mt. Mabu in Mozambique inspired a four-player version of Gulugufe, traditionally a two-player game. Play with the concept of negation as you flip your caterpillar pieces and strategically move them across the board to capture opponents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Lemurs, the national animal of Madagascar, show you how to move the pieces in Fanorona, a two-player game from the country. Add in the lemurs&amp;rsquo; ages and you can use the mathematical concept of comparison to strategically knock off opponents&amp;rsquo; pieces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
